The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks for automatic detection of metastases in lymph nodes from digital whole-slide images. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a cloud computing platform for training and evaluation, which could also fall under information retrieval (cs.IR).
